{
  // robot.info v0.1 — Mnemo Cortex
  //
  // Structured product manifest for AI agents. Paired with robot.install
  // (setup) and llms.txt (docs index). Spec: ./ROBOT-INFO-SPEC.md.
  //
  // Single JSON object, UTF-8. JavaScript-style // line comments are
  // stripped before parsing — manifests stay annotatable.

  "robot_info_version": "0.2",

  "name": "Mnemo Cortex",
  "tagline": "Cognitive coprocessor with active memory for AI agents — local-first, decay-aware, cross-agent dreaming.",
  "summary": "Cognitive coprocessor with active memory that gives AI agents persistent recall across sessions. Local SQLite + FTS5 working memory plus a structured Facts table (entity/attribute/value triples with a three-state confidence ladder) for the lookups semantic search gets wrong. Every memory record carries provenance (source + category) and decays on a category-aware schedule — topology facts age fast, doctrine stays perpetual, and recall returns a structured stale_warning when a fact is past its threshold so the agent verifies before acting. Cross-agent dreaming synthesizes every connected agent's memories into a shared nightly brief.",
  "backstory": "Guy Hutchins started exploring AI memory with ChatGPT 3.5 using basic text files. When OpenClaw launched and needed better memory, he gave Opie (Claude) a simple prompt: \"If you were a ClawdBot and your user wanted you to have the best memory you could build yourself, what would it look like?\" Opie was on extended thinking and just built it — no clarifying questions, no spec, just shipped a working memory system. Guy gave the same prompt to AL (ChatGPT), who built his own version independently. AL saw Opie's and said it was more in depth. Opie saw AL's and said it had ideas worth blending. The two versions merged. When it came time to name it, the first two suggestions were \"Mnemo\" and \"Cortex.\" Guy picked both. Mnemo Cortex.",
  "version": "4.9.12",
  "license": "MIT",
  "homepage": "https://projectsparks.ai/mnemo-cortex",
  "source": "https://github.com/GuyMannDude/mnemo-cortex",
  "contact": "guy@projectsparks.ai",
  "maintainer": "Project Sparks",

  "capabilities": [
    "Persistent semantic memory across agent sessions (~sub-100ms local recall on a 4k-record corpus).",
    "Indexed sqlite-vec backend (v2.11.0) — per-agent vec0 virtual table answers k-NN semantic queries in ~3ms on a 1.4k-record corpus, replacing the linear-scan cosine pass.",
    "v3 provenance tagging — every record carries source (user|tool|inferred|brain|migrated) and category (topology, doctrine, incident, identity, relationship, decision, current_state, session_log, unknown).",
    "Category-aware decay — topology warns at 30d / stale at 90d; doctrine, incident, identity, decision are perpetual.",
    "Structured stale_warning field on recall — programmatic enforcement, not advisory prose.",
    "Regex-based category auto-suggester at write time — zero-cost, deterministic, returns matched keywords so the agent learns the conventions.",
    "Filterable recall — by source, category, age, and stale-severity.",
    "Structured Facts (v3.0 / Phase 3) — (entity, attribute, value) triples in a local SQLite store with a three-state confidence ladder (verified > high_probability > false). Sub-millisecond exact lookup for the cases semantic search gets wrong (names, settings, entity attributes). Append-only audit history per fact; contradictions emit a notification over the bus + Discord webhook.",
    "Dreamer Stage 0.5 — nightly automated fact extraction from the day's memories using a conservative direct-statements-only prompt; new facts post at confidence='high_probability', conflicts with existing 'verified' facts get rejected and batched into an end-of-run notification.",
    "Cross-agent dreaming — nightly synthesis of every connected agent's memories into a shared brief.",
    "WikAI — auto-compiled knowledge base regenerated nightly from Mnemo data.",
    "Embedding hosted fallback — embeddings default to local Ollama (nomic-embed-text). If Ollama is unreachable, recall queries fall back to hosted Google Gemini embeddings (Matryoshka-truncated to match the 768-dim store width) so reads keep working; saves refuse-and-alert instead of falling back (v4.9.9), because a different model's vectors occupy a different embedding space and storing them would corrupt the index.",
    "Per-agent memory namespaces — shared, isolated, or hybrid deployments.",
    "OAuth 2.1 Resource Server mode for remote MCP clients (Auth0-compatible).",
    "Developer Dump — JSONL trace of every MCP tool call through the bridge (tool, params, response, latency, ok/error). Off by default; flip on with MNEMO_DUMP=on. One file per agent per day, greppable with jq. CLI: mnemo-cortex dump list / dump tail <agent>.",
    "Trajectory store (v4.5–4.7) — save/recall procedural how-to recipes separate from episodic memory; the nightly Dreamer distills strategy lessons (successes AND failures) from real session streams, and recall reinforcement tracks which recipes actually get used.",
    "Scoped tokens (v4.9.0) — per-tenant, per-endpoint bearer credentials beside the master key; only pin-enforcing endpoints can be allowlisted, enforced at config load, constant-time compares throughout.",
    "Embedding task-type prefixes (v4.6.0) — nomic search_document/search_query asymmetry applied inside the provider; one-command all-tenant reindex CLI (migrate reindex).",
    "Category pushdown into the vec index (#468, v4.9.2) — category-filtered k-NN inside sqlite-vec with widened-overfetch escalation; routine recalls on a 6k-record store went 23s → sub-second.",
    "idea category + recall mode=explore (v4.8.0) — creative seeds get their own decay class and a serendipity recall lens; the Muse (analyst sibling, gated off by default) auditions idea extraction from live session streams.",
    "GET /dream/latest (v4.9.3) — the nightly dream brief served from the Cortex host, so agents on any machine boot with the shared overnight synthesis.",
    "Aesthetic-technique distillation (v4.9.4) — the Stage 0.7 judge recognizes creative choices as distillable strategies under the cross-cutting art-technique task class; recall_trajectory(task_type=art-technique) briefs any art session.",
    "Tenant-path hardening + fail-closed auth (v4.9.5) — agent_id is validated at every path boundary (no traversal/absolute escapes), and the server refuses to bind a non-loopback interface with no auth configured unless explicitly opted in.",
    "session_id path hardening (v4.9.6) — the transcript read path validates session_id the same way as agent_id, so a request cannot read arbitrary *.jsonl files off disk via traversal/absolute ids.",
    "Loss-proof capture pipeline (v4.9.7) — the session watcher's read offset is a commit record (torn JSONL lines, mid-write polls, and failed /ingest calls all retry instead of silently dropping exchanges), /ingest dedups client retries by content hash, and the offline writeback queue + bus failure path fail loudly instead of black-holing data.",
    "Embedding-space integrity (v4.9.9) — an empty embedder response is an error (it can no longer lock the pipeline's dimension to 0 and brick saves until restart), and vectors bound for the index (writeback, trajectory save, dreamer) never fall back to a different model: foreign-space vectors are refused with an alert instead of being written as unrecallable noise, while recall queries still fall back freely."
  ],

  "exposes": {
    "rest_api": {
      "default_port": 50001,
      "base_path": "/",
      "endpoints": [
        {"path": "/health", "method": "GET", "purpose": "Heartbeat — returns provider status, model IDs, memory count."},
        {"path": "/context", "method": "POST", "purpose": "Semantic recall with v3 filters (source, category, exclude_stale, max_age_days). Returns chunks with structured stale_warning when applicable."},
        {"path": "/writeback", "method": "POST", "purpose": "Save a memory with optional source/category/additional_tags. Returns category_used + category_suggested + match_keywords."},
        {"path": "/preflight", "method": "POST", "purpose": "Score an agent's draft response against memory context — PASS / ENRICH / WARN / BLOCK verdict."},
        {"path": "/trajectory/save", "method": "POST", "purpose": "Store a procedural recipe (task_type, steps, rating, provenance) in the trajectory store."},
        {"path": "/trajectory/recall", "method": "POST", "purpose": "Semantic recall over stored trajectories with min_rating / task_type filters; bumps reinforcement stats."},
        {"path": "/dream/latest", "method": "GET", "purpose": "Newest nightly dream brief (date, age_hours, markdown content) served from the Cortex host."},
        {"path": "/vec/status", "method": "GET", "purpose": "Vec index health per tenant — indexed count vs memory entries on disk."},
        {"path": "/vec/backfill", "method": "POST", "purpose": "Embed-and-index memories missing from the vec index (adaptive truncation, breaker-bypassed)."},
        {"path": "/facts/{entity}/{attribute}", "method": "GET", "purpose": "Look up a single structured fact by (entity, attribute). Sub-millisecond exact lookup."},
        {"path": "/facts", "method": "GET", "purpose": "Filtered fact list — by entity, attribute, value_contains, confidence."},
        {"path": "/facts", "method": "POST", "purpose": "Assert a fact. Promotion ladder enforced: verified > high_probability > false; lower confidence rejected if existing is higher."},
        {"path": "/facts/demote", "method": "POST", "purpose": "Mark a fact false without supplying a replacement value (escape hatch when the correct value isn't known yet)."},
        {"path": "/facts/history/{entity}/{attribute}", "method": "GET", "purpose": "Read the append-only audit log of every change to a fact pair."},
        {"path": "/facts/contradictions", "method": "GET", "purpose": "List per-run conflicts where Stage 0.5 extracted a fact that disagreed with an existing verified fact."},
        {"path": "/mcp", "method": "POST", "purpose": "MCP Streamable HTTP facade (OAuth 2.1 Resource Server mode for remote clients)."}
      ]
    },
    "mcp_tools": [
      {"name": "mnemo_recall", "purpose": "Recall memories scoped to the calling agent. Supports v3 source/category/exclude_stale filters. Returns inline ⚠️ STALE banner when chunks exceed their decay threshold."},
      {"name": "mnemo_save", "purpose": "Save a memory with optional v3 provenance fields. Bridge auto-suggests category from content if omitted, returning the suggestion + matched keywords so the agent learns."},
      {"name": "mnemo_search", "purpose": "Cross-agent semantic search (gated by share mode). Same filter surface as mnemo_recall."},
      {"name": "mnemo_share", "purpose": "Toggle cross-agent sharing for the current session."},
      {"name": "mnemo_fact_get", "purpose": "Look up a single structured fact by (entity, attribute). Sub-millisecond exact lookup with confidence + evidence source."},
      {"name": "mnemo_fact_query", "purpose": "Filtered fact list by entity / attribute / value_contains / confidence."},
      {"name": "mnemo_fact_save", "purpose": "Assert a fact triple. Promotion ladder enforced (verified > high_probability > false); contradictions with an existing verified fact emit a bus + Discord notification."},
      {"name": "mnemo_fact_demote", "purpose": "Mark a fact false without supplying a replacement — the escape hatch for the verified → false transition when the correct value isn't yet known."},
      {"name": "agent_startup", "purpose": "Neutral session-boot tool (BRAIN_DIR gated) — loads the calling agent's lane file + cross-agent docs + recent memories + last dream brief."},
      {"name": "opie_startup", "purpose": "Legacy alias of agent_startup pinned to Opie's lane. Behaves identically except for the identity-header text and the lane filename it loads."},
      {"name": "session_end", "purpose": "Drains auto-capture, saves a summary, commits the agent's brain lane. Tags as source=user, category=current_state."},
      {"name": "read_brain_file", "purpose": "Read a file from the agent's brain repo (when BRAIN_DIR is configured)."},
      {"name": "write_brain_file", "purpose": "Write/update a file in the agent's brain repo."},
      {"name": "list_brain_files", "purpose": "List files in the agent's brain repo, optionally filtered by subdirectory."},
      {"name": "wiki_search", "purpose": "Search the WikAI compiled knowledge base (WIKI_DIR gated)."},
      {"name": "wiki_read", "purpose": "Read a specific WikAI page by path."},
      {"name": "wiki_index", "purpose": "List the top-level structure of the wiki (projects / entities / concepts / sources)."},
      {"name": "passport_observe_behavior", "purpose": "Submit a behavioral observation about an agent through the Passport pipeline (32 detectors + review queue)."},
      {"name": "passport_get_user_context", "purpose": "Read the current agent's promoted Passport observations."},
      {"name": "passport_list_pending_observations", "purpose": "List Passport observations awaiting review with detector verdicts."},
      {"name": "passport_promote_observation", "purpose": "Promote a pending Passport observation into the agent's stable context."},
      {"name": "passport_forget_or_override", "purpose": "Remove a Passport claim from the agent's context, or override it with a corrected version."}
    ],
    "cli": [
      {"command": "mnemo-cortex init", "purpose": "Interactive setup wizard — provider, models, agents."},
      {"command": "mnemo-cortex start [--foreground] [--port P]", "purpose": "Start the bridge as a daemon (or attached)."},
      {"command": "mnemo-cortex stop", "purpose": "Stop the running daemon."},
      {"command": "mnemo-cortex status", "purpose": "Report daemon state, PID, port, memory count."},
      {"command": "mnemo-cortex doctor", "purpose": "Diagnostic — connectivity to providers, disk state, schema version."}
    ]
  },

  "install": {
    "robot_install": "./robot.install",
    "robot_install_sh": "./robot-install.sh",
    "manual_docs": "https://github.com/GuyMannDude/mnemo-cortex#install-guide",
    "platforms": ["linux", "macos", "windows-wsl2"],
    "runtime": "python>=3.11",
    "dependencies": ["fastapi>=0.115", "uvicorn>=0.30", "pydantic>=2.8", "numpy>=1.24", "httpx>=0.25", "pyyaml>=6.0"],
    "facts_seed": {
      "tool": "./tools/seed-facts.py",
      "example": "./tools/seed-facts.example.yaml",
      "docs": "./tools/README.md",
      "purpose": "Seed the Phase 3 Facts table from a YAML of canonical truths so exact lookups don't lose to stale fuzzy recall. Opt-in via the robot.install facts_seed block (disabled by default); also installable as a git post-commit hook and/or nightly cron to stay in sync."
    }
  },

  "compatibility": {
    "mcp_hosts": [
      "Claude Desktop",
      "Claude Code",
      "OpenClaw",
      "LM Studio",
      "AnythingLLM",
      "Agent Zero (Docker)",
      "Ollama (via MCPHost or ollmcp)",
      "Hermes Agent",
      "Open WebUI",
      "llama.cpp",
      "LobeChat",
      "Jan"
    ],
    "models": "Any LLM with tool-use support. Embedding via Ollama (nomic-embed-text) or OpenAI / Google cloud fallback. Reasoning (preflight/compaction) via Ollama or any OpenAI-compatible provider (OpenRouter, Anthropic, Google).",
    "protocols": ["MCP/2025-03-26", "OAuth 2.1 RS (RFC 9728)", "Streamable HTTP transport"]
  },

  "privacy": {
    "telemetry": "none",
    "data_location": "Local disk by default (~/.mnemo-cortex/ or ~/.agentb/). SQLite + JSON memory files. Per-agent subdirectories.",
    "auth": "Loopback-only by default (127.0.0.1). Optional X-API-Key for non-localhost binds (legacy sk-mnemo-* tokens). OAuth 2.1 Resource Server mode for remote MCP clients (Auth0-compatible).",
    "outbound_calls": [
      "Reasoning provider for preflight + compaction (configurable; default OpenRouter; only fires on /preflight calls and during compaction passes).",
      "Embedding provider for semantic indexing (default Ollama localhost; hosted Google Gemini embeddings as automatic fallback when Ollama is unreachable, Matryoshka-truncated to the 768-dim store width).",
      "Bus + Discord webhook for fact-contradiction notifications when Dreamer Stage 0.5 finds a conflict with an existing verified fact (only fires on conflict; no per-message chatter)."
    ]
  },

  "related": [
    {"name": "FrankenClaw", "url": "https://github.com/GuyMannDude/frankenclaw", "purpose": "MCP tool chassis — build your own agent tools in ~5 minutes (drop a Python file in tools/, flip it on). Ships one example tool (web_scrape). Pairs with Mnemo (memory) to give an agent both recall and hands."},
    {"name": "Cortex Harness", "url": "https://github.com/GuyMannDude/cortex-harness", "purpose": "Forkable, generic AI-agent framework built on the Mnemo Cortex memory layer. Pick a vertical, edit one config file, build a memory-backed agent."},
    {"name": "Disco-Bus", "url": "https://github.com/GuyMannDude/disco-bus", "purpose": "Push-based agent-to-agent messaging mesh. Pair with Mnemo for multi-agent setups where agents need both shared memory and direct communication."},
    {"name": "llms.txt", "url": "./llms.txt", "purpose": "LLM-friendly documentation index (llmstxt.org convention)."},
    {"name": "robot.install", "url": "./robot.install", "purpose": "Non-interactive install manifest for this product."},
    {"name": "THE-LANE-PROTOCOL.md", "url": "./THE-LANE-PROTOCOL.md", "purpose": "Operating practice for running agents with persistent memory — the protocol that pairs with this product."}
  ],

  "common_questions": [
    {
      "q": "What is Mnemo Cortex?",
      "a": "A local-first cognitive coprocessor with active memory for AI agents. It gives agents persistent semantic recall across sessions, decay-aware so old facts age out automatically, and cross-agent dreaming so a team of agents can share what they've learned overnight. MIT licensed, runs on your machine, $0 in API costs if you use Ollama."
    },
    {
      "q": "Is it free?",
      "a": "Yes — MIT open source, runs entirely on local hardware. If you use Ollama for reasoning + embedding it costs $0. Cloud providers (OpenRouter, OpenAI, Google) are optional fallbacks."
    },
    {
      "q": "How is it different from Mem0, Zep, or Letta?",
      "a": "Mnemo runs entirely local with no required cloud component, supports multiple agents sharing memory natively (cross-agent dreaming — the only AI memory system that does this), ships a v3 provenance/decay system that explicitly distinguishes user-stated facts from agent-inferred ones, and pairs semantic recall with a structured Facts table for the lookups search gets wrong. Mem0, Zep, and Letta are excellent but store memory per-agent, are cloud-first or cloud-only, and don't synthesize across agents."
    },
    {
      "q": "Does it work with Claude Code?",
      "a": "Yes — integrations/claude-code/ has a ~60-second install. Mnemo gives CC fluid memory across sessions; CC's own memory only lives within a session."
    },
    {
      "q": "Does it work with Claude Desktop?",
      "a": "Yes — drag-and-drop .mcpb bundle in integrations/claude-desktop/. No clone, no Node, no JSON editing. Windows, macOS, Linux."
    },
    {
      "q": "Does it work with my local LLM?",
      "a": "If your host speaks MCP, yes. Verified: LM Studio, AnythingLLM, OpenClaw, Hermes Agent, Open WebUI, llama.cpp, LobeChat, Jan, Agent Zero (Docker), Ollama (via MCPHost or ollmcp). Any tool-capable model works."
    },
    {
      "q": "What does the v3 decay system do?",
      "a": "Every memory record now carries provenance (source: user|tool|inferred|brain|migrated) and category (topology, doctrine, incident, identity, relationship, decision, current_state, session_log, unknown). Topology decays fast — warn at 30 days, stale at 90 — because IPs and ports change. Doctrine, incident, identity, and decision are perpetual. Recall returns a structured stale_warning field when a record exceeds its category's threshold, so an agent code-paths around it instead of trusting a 3-month-old fact."
    },
    {
      "q": "What are Structured Facts (the v3.0 / Phase 3 addition)?",
      "a": "Semantic search is great until your agent needs to remember a visitor's name — that's a key-value lookup, not a fuzzy match. Facts store (entity, attribute, value) triples in a local SQLite table with a three-state confidence ladder (verified > high_probability > false). Sub-millisecond reads, four MCP tools (mnemo_fact_save / mnemo_fact_get / mnemo_fact_query / mnemo_fact_demote), and an append-only audit history per fact. When a new fact contradicts an existing verified one, Mnemo fires a bus + Discord notification so the owning agent can adjudicate. Dreamer Stage 0.5 runs nightly to extract conservative direct-statement facts from the day's memories automatically."
    },
    {
      "q": "How do I seed the Facts table so recall stops drifting?",
      "a": "An empty Facts table is the trap: a fuzzy session-log memory wins a lookup it should lose, so an agent 'remembers' a stale value because nothing canonical contradicted it. Seed the truths you already know. Copy tools/seed-facts.example.yaml to seed-facts.yaml, fill in your (entity, attribute, value) rows, and run tools/seed-facts.py — each becomes a verified Fact that outranks contradicting recall. It's idempotent (re-runs skip matches, flag conflicts). Enable the robot.install facts_seed block to seed at install, and optionally wire the post-commit hook + nightly cron (tools/) so the table re-seeds whenever your YAML changes. See tools/README.md."
    },
    {
      "q": "What does the regex auto-suggester do?",
      "a": "When you save a memory without specifying a category, a regex over the summary + key_facts picks one and returns it in the save response with the matched keywords. Deterministic, zero cost, zero latency. The agent sees what was picked and can override on the next save if it was wrong."
    },
    {
      "q": "Can I run isolated namespaces per customer?",
      "a": "Yes. Each agent has its own memory namespace under agents.NAME in the config. Shared / isolated / hybrid (shared internal + isolated customer-facing) deployments are all supported."
    },
    {
      "q": "How do I install it without prompts (CI / agent install)?",
      "a": "Run ./robot-install.sh. It reads robot.install (JSON manifest with sensible defaults) and emits a single JSON object on stdout. Exit 0 = success. Full schema in the README under 'Non-interactive install.'"
    },
    {
      "q": "What's the auth model?",
      "a": "Loopback-only by default — 127.0.0.1, no auth required. For non-localhost binds you can use legacy sk-mnemo-* API keys via X-API-Key header, or OAuth 2.1 Resource Server mode (Auth0-compatible) for remote MCP clients."
    },
    {
      "q": "Does it phone home?",
      "a": "No telemetry. Outbound calls only happen to providers you configure — reasoning + embedding (configurable, defaults to local Ollama; hosted Google Gemini embeddings auto-fall-back only if Ollama is unreachable). One conditional outbound: Discord webhook for fact-contradiction notifications, off unless you wire a webhook URL."
    },
    {
      "q": "What's THE-LANE-PROTOCOL.md and do I need to read it?",
      "a": "It's the operating practice for running agents with persistent memory — a 6-step ritual that makes every cold start feel warm. Mnemo is the memory store; the Lane Protocol is the loop that makes it pay off. Worth 5 minutes per session if you're running multi-agent setups."
    },
    {
      "q": "What's Dreaming?",
      "a": "Nightly cross-agent synthesis. Every connected agent's memories from the day get summarized into a single brief that each agent reads at startup. No manual relay between agents — they wake up knowing what the others did. The only AI memory system that does this."
    }
  ],

  // ─── v0.2 user-facing layer ──────────────────────────────────────────
  // Plain-language sections an AI reads to explain Mnemo to a non-developer
  // user. Written for the human on the other side of the AI, not for a dev.

  // Read when a user asks "what is this?" / "why would I use it?"
  "why": "Your AI forgets everything between conversations. Every new session starts from zero — no memory of what you discussed, what you decided, what you built together. Mnemo Cortex fixes that: it gives your AI persistent memory that survives across sessions. Save the context that matters, recall it later, and let your agents consolidate what they learned overnight while you sleep. It runs on your own machine, your data stays in a file you own, and it's free with a local model.",

  // Read when a user asks "how do I install this?" Written for someone who
  // has never opened a terminal. The easiest real path is the Claude Desktop
  // one-click bundle (no clone, no Node, no JSON editing).
  "install_steps": [
    {"step": 1, "instruction": "Decide where Mnemo runs. The simplest setup runs it right on your own computer — no server, no cloud account."},
    {"step": 2, "instruction": "If you use Claude Desktop: download the one-click '.mcpb' bundle from integrations/claude-desktop/ and drag it onto Claude Desktop's Settings → Extensions. No cloning, no Node, no config files to edit. Works on Windows, macOS, and Linux."},
    {"step": 3, "instruction": "If you use Claude Code (the terminal tool): follow the 60-second guide in integrations/claude-code/ — one command wires Mnemo in as a memory tool."},
    {"step": 4, "instruction": "For anything scripted or hands-off (CI, an AI agent installing it for you): run ./robot-install.sh. It reads the robot.install manifest, sets everything up with zero prompts, and prints a JSON result. Exit 0 means it worked."},
    {"step": 5, "instruction": "To run it free with no cloud calls, install Ollama first (ollama.com) — Mnemo uses it for the local AI work. Cloud providers (OpenRouter, OpenAI, Google) are optional fallbacks if you'd rather not run a local model."}
  ],

  // Read when a user asks "does this work with X?" Name + how to connect.
  "works_with": [
    {"name": "Claude Desktop", "how": "One-click .mcpb bundle — integrations/claude-desktop/. No clone, no JSON editing."},
    {"name": "Claude Code", "how": "60-second install — integrations/claude-code/. Gives CC memory that persists across sessions."},
    {"name": "LM Studio", "how": "Native MCP, configured in the GUI — integrations/lmstudio/."},
    {"name": "AnythingLLM", "how": "Add as an MCP server; chat mode fires the tools automatically — integrations/anythingllm/."},
    {"name": "Hermes Agent", "how": "First-class MCP (Hermes v0.12.0+) — integrations/hermes/."},
    {"name": "Agent Zero", "how": "In-container MCP for autonomous Docker agents — integrations/agent-zero/."},
    {"name": "Ollama / Open WebUI / llama.cpp / LobeChat / Jan", "how": "Any MCP-capable host connects through the same Node bridge. See the README integrations section."},
    {"name": "FrankenClaw", "how": "Sibling product (not coupled): FrankenClaw gives agents hands (search, vision, browser); Mnemo gives them memory. Pair them for a fully-equipped agent."},
    {"name": "Disco-Bus", "how": "Sibling product (not coupled): Disco-Bus is agent-to-agent messaging. Pair with Mnemo when agents need both shared memory and direct comms."}
  ],

  // Read when a user asks "how do I customize / extend this?"
  "extensibility": "Mnemo is an MCP server, so any AI platform that speaks MCP can connect to it. The memory lives in SQLite files you own — back them up, move them, inspect them with any SQLite tool. Brain files are plain markdown you edit in any text editor. The nightly Dreamer is a Python script you can customize or replace. The Facts seeder (tools/) is a small YAML-driven script. Everything is MIT-licensed and built to be modified.",

  // The hidden 80% — things users rarely discover from docs. An AI surfaces
  // these when timely, not as a feature dump.
  "tips": [
    "Mnemo isn't locked to localhost. Run it on one machine and point agents on other machines (or other family members' laptops) at the same address — they'll share memory.",
    "Brain files are the place for rules your AI should always follow. Put 'never delete files without asking' in a brain file and every session boots with that rule loaded.",
    "When your AI needs an exact value — a person's name, a port number, a model ID — that's a job for the Facts table, not fuzzy recall. Seed the truths you already know with tools/seed-facts.py so recall stops drifting to stale guesses.",
    "Dreaming runs best with Ollama local — the overnight consolidation happens on your hardware, free, and nothing leaves your machine.",
    "Cross-agent memory means one AI can save research and a different AI can use it later. They never have to be in the same conversation.",
    "Every recalled memory carries a stale-warning when it's past its category's age threshold, so your AI knows to double-check a three-month-old IP instead of trusting it blindly."
  ],

